originalText.text: I just called to make an appointment for Dr. Warschauer was floored to find out he passed away in June 2023. He was a great doctor caring and very professional. He was so encouraging to me during my surgery and aftercare. May he rest in peace.

originalText.text:
Dr. Craig Warschauer was an excellent internist and cardiologist.  Also, a true gem of a person, constantly working and caring for his patients and others. Thoughtful and clear with his explanations. Always willing to give the time needed to his patients.

I will miss him.

originalText.text:
I am in total shock today just found out that Dr. Warschauer had passed away.
He was great man and we always had fun conversations. He loved basketball and his dog.
I met him when I was in need of medical assistance. And our friendship grew from there. We talked every couple of months. RIP my friend
Albert King

originalText.text: I was very impressed with the level of care provided by Dr. Warschauer and I thought his staff did a great job in checking me in and completing the preliminary screening. In response to other comments, you are correct that the waiting room is dark but I've been to "prettier" offices where the doctors treated me condescendingly. I measure the worth of a doctor by the care I receive, not whether I can check my phone in the waiting room, and in that regard, Dr. W's concern for his patients is second to none. He's a straight shooter and I wouldn't go elsewhere.

originalText.text:
Dr Warschauer seemed good.

Office visit experience not great. No internet service in the space (can easily get a booster), offer hot water in cooler but cups emit plastic grease when hot water is poured, long wait even though office empty and no patients going in/coming out, office staff rude and pushing cardiac screening on me even though my doc didn’t ask for it, and office itself could use a facelift.
